GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 2
SENATE BILL 131
Finance Committee Substitute Adopted 4/9/25
Short Title: Temp. Local Sales Tax Changes/Buncombe Co. (Local)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
February 24, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO TEMPORARILY MODIFY BUNCOMBE COUNTY'S USE OF ONE-HALF OF
3 ARTICLE 39 LOCAL SALES AND USE TAX PROCEEDS TO INCLUDE BOTH
4 SCHOOL CAPITAL OUTLAY AND SCHOOL OPERATING EXPENSES AND TO
5 MAKE TECHNICAL CHANGES TO THE BUNCOMBE SCHOOL CAPITAL FUND
6 COMMISSION.
7 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
8
9 TEMPORARILY MODIFY DISTRIBUTION AND USE OF ONE-HALF OF THE NET
10 PROCEEDS FROM THE FIRST ONE CENT OF LOCAL SALES AND USE TAX
11 ALLOCATED TO BUNCOMBE COUNTY
12 SECTION 1.(a) Notwithstanding Section 6 of Chapter 134 of the 1983 Session
13 Laws, as amended by Chapter 534 of the 1983 Session Laws and S.L. 2016-19, directing that
14 one-half of the local government sales and use tax revenue be distributed to the School Capital
15 Fund Commission for Buncombe County (Commission), the Secretary of Revenue shall
16 distribute one hundred percent (100%) of the net proceeds of the local government sales and use
17 tax revenue collected by Buncombe County under Article 39 of Chapter 105 of the General
18 Statutes in accordance with G.S. 105-472 using the ad valorem method of distribution.
19 Notwithstanding the provision in G.S. 105-472 allowing counties to change the method of
20 distribution, Buncombe County is not permitted to change the method of distribution for any year
21 for which the distribution and use provisions of this act apply.
22 SECTION 1.(b) Notwithstanding the use provisions in Sections 9 through 12 of
23 Chapter 134 of the 1983 Session Laws, as amended by Chapter 534 of the 1983 Session Laws
24 and S.L. 2016-19, and applicable to the funds distributed to the Commission, Buncombe County
25 shall use the net proceeds of the local government sales and use tax revenue collected under
26 Article 39 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes and allocated to Buncombe County under
27 subsection (a) of this section as follows:
28 (1) Fifty percent (50%) for school capital outlay purposes, as defined in
29 G.S. 115C-426(f), or to retire any indebtedness incurred by the County for
30 these purposes, and for school operating expenses. The Commission shall
31 serve in an advisory capacity to the Buncombe County Board of County
32 Commissioners with respect to the use of funds under this subdivision for
33 school capital outlay purposes by considering the capital needs of both the
34 Buncombe County School System and the Asheville City School System,
35 prioritizing those needs, and recommending projects to be funded. However,
*S131-v-2*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 the use of funds under this subdivision shall not be under the control of the
2 Commission and shall be determined by the board of commissioners.
3 (2) Fifty percent (50%) for any public purpose.
4 SECTION 1.(c) This section applies only to Buncombe County.
5 SECTION 1.(d) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to net
6 proceeds distributed to Buncombe County by the Secretary of Revenue under Article 39 of
7 Chapter 105 of the General Statutes on or after July 1, 2025, and expires on June 30, 2027.
8
9 MAKE TECHNICAL CHANGES TO BUNCOMBE SCHOOL CAPITAL FUND
10 COMMISSION
11 SECTION 2. Chapter 134 of the 1983 Session Laws, as amended by Chapter 534 of
12 the 1983 Session Laws and S.L. 2016-19, is recodified as Section 3 of this act and reads as
13 rewritten:
14 "Section 1. There is hereby created a Commission to be known as the School Capital Fund
15 Commission for Buncombe County, which Commission shall have and possess all the powers
16 conferred by this act and such other powers as may be useful or necessary to permit it fully to
17 carry out the purposes of this act. The Commission is hereby declared to be a corporation with
18 perpetual succession, the right to adopt and use a corporate seal, to sue and to be sued, and to
19 hold, manage and control the moneys and properties received by it under the provisions of this
20 act. It shall have the right to make reasonable rules and regulations for the conduct of its business.
21 "Sec. 2. The Commission shall consist of five members. Members of the Commission shall
22 serve two-year terms and shall be appointed as follows: one appointed by the Asheville City
23 Board of Education, one appointed by the Buncombe County Board of Education, two appointed
24 by the Buncombe County Board of Commissioners, and one appointed by the other four
25 appointees. A member appointed by a local governing board or a school board shall serve at the
26 pleasure of that board. The member appointed by the other appointees shall serve at the pleasure
27 of the majority of the other appointees. Any vacancy shall be filled by the appointing authority
28 of the member creating the vacancy to fill the unexpired term.
29 "Sec. 3. A quorum shall be three members of the Commission.
30 "Sec. 4. The Commission shall organize, adopt bylaws or rules and regulations to govern its
31 procedure and the conduct of the business and affairs of the Commission and appoint a chairman
32 and vice-chairman from among its membership who shall serve a one-year term and appoint a
33 secretary for a one-year term and until their successors are appointed by the Commission. The
34 finance officer for Buncombe County shall be the finance officer of the Commission. The county
35 finance officer shall give bond for the faithful performance of his duties as the finance officer of
36 the Commission in an amount determined by the Commission. The finance officer of the
37 Commission shall manage the funds of the Commission only as directed by the Commission. The
38 Commission may select and appoint an attorney of the Commission to serve at the pleasure of
39 the Commission. The Commission may fix the compensation for the attorney.
40 "Sec. 5. Regular or stated meetings of the Commission shall be held at such time and place
41 as may be provided by the Commission in its bylaws or rules and regulations, and special
42 meetings may be held on the call of the chairman after due notice.
43 "Sec. 6. One half One-half of any local government sales and use tax revenue distributed to
44 Buncombe County under G.S. 105-472 shall be paid to the Commission by the Secretary of
45 Revenue; provided that if distribution of the local government sales and use tax revenue is made
46 under G.S. 105-472(2), (the ad valorem method), then taxing districts shall receive their funds
47 under G.S. 105-472(2) as if no funds had been paid to the Commission by the Secretary of
48 Revenue, and in computing what amount is one-half of the sales and use tax revenue, the
49 Secretary of Revenue shall not reduce the total by the amount to be distributed to the taxing
50 districts. This section does not affect the distribution of any local or State sales and use tax
51 revenue to the municipalities in Buncombe County.
Page 2 Senate Bill 131-Second Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "Sec. 7. Repealed by Section 1 of Session Laws 2016-19, effective June 21, 2016.
2 "Sec. 8. Any other capital funds appropriated by Buncombe County new estimated to cost
3 in excess of one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) at any one location 10 pursuant to Article
4 40 and Article 42 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes shall be apportioned among the
5 Asheville City Board of Education and the Buncombe County Board of Education according to
6 the membership of each unit using the process set forth in G.S. 115C-430. Buncombe County
7 shall maintain separate internal accounts for each school board in order to comply with this
8 section. These funds are not under the control of the School Capital Fund Commission.
9 "Sec. 9. All funds received by the Commission under Section 6 of this act shall be placed in
10 a capital reserve fund as provided in Part 2 of Article 3 of Chapter 159 of the General Statutes.
11 The capital reserve fund shall be known as the Public School Capital Needs Fund.
12 "Sec. 10. All funds in the Public School Capital Needs Fund shall be used to finance new
13 public school of any amount, construction, to finance public school improvement and renovation
14 projects that exceed one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000), estimated to cost in excess of one
15 hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) at any one location, or to retire any indebtedness incurred
16 by the county after July 1, 1983 for these purposes.
17 The Commission shall consider the capital needs of both the Buncombe County School
18 System and the Asheville City School System, prioritize those needs, and recommend projects
19 to be funded from the Public School Capital Needs Fund to the board of county commissioners
20 based on the priority of needs determined.
21 By joint agreement of the Board of County Commissioners and both boards of education,
22 money may be transferred from the account under this section of one board of education to the
23 account under this section of the other board of education, provided that the agreement must
24 require a transfer back of an equal amount of funds at some fixed date in the future, plus a sum
25 to be determined at that date which represents interest which would have accrued on the funds if
26 they had remained in the first account.
27 "Sec. 11. Moneys in the Public School Capital Needs Fund shall be subject to appropriation
28 by the board of county commissioners. The Commission shall disburse such moneys as a
29 ministerial duty upon receiving a written request from the board of county commissioners after
30 the county board of commissioners has adopted an ordinance and after receipt of a written request
31 from the appropriate board of education indicating it is prepared to enter into a contract, and
32 G.S. 115C-521 shall continue to apply.
33 "Sec. 11.1. Notwithstanding any other provision of this act, if the Buncombe County Board
34 of Commissioners appropriates any federal revenue sharing funds to the Commission for the
35 purpose of substituting revenue sharing funds for sales tax funds, then it must at the same time
36 appropriate from the Commission to the county an equal amount of funds received under Section
37 6 to be used for such purposes as the Board of Commissioners shall deem appropriate and are
38 otherwise authorized by law, provided that such federal revenue sharing funds shall be divided
39 pro rata under Section 10 of this act.
40 "Sec. 12. The reasonable and necessary expenses of the Commission, including the
41 compensation of its officers and employees and the cost of any bond required by it, shall be paid
42 by the County of Buncombe. The chairman of the Commission shall, on or about the first day of
43 each calendar month, certify to the governing body of Buncombe County the expenses of the
44 Commission incurred during the preceding month, and the governing body of the county shall
45 forthwith, and within five days thereafter, cause to be paid to the Commission the expenses
46 required to be paid. All such payments shall be charged to the general fund of the county."
47
48 EFFECTIVE DATE
49 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
50 law.
